================================================================================
PHASE 1 — PROJECT SETUP
================================================================================
Goal: Scaffold a production-grade Next.js 14+ App Router monorepo with strict
      TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, ESLint, Prettier, and a clean folder structure.
      Nothing runs client-side that shouldn't. Environment variables are handled
      safely from day one.

--- 1.1  Prerequisites ---
[x] Install Node.js 20 LTS  (v22.13.1 installed)
[x] Install pnpm            (v11.1.3 installed via npm install -g pnpm)
[x] Install Git             (v2.47.0 installed)
[x] Install VS Code + extensions: ESLint, Prettier, Tailwind CSS IntelliSense,
    Prisma (optional), Thunder Client or REST Client

--- 1.2  Bootstrap Project ---
[x] Run: npx create-next-app@latest qr-ticket-app \
           --typescript \
           --tailwind \
           --eslint \
           --app \
           --src-dir \
           --import-alias "@/*"
[x] cd qr-ticket-app

--- 1.3  Install Core Dependencies ---
[x] pnpm add @supabase/supabase-js @supabase/ssr
[x] pnpm add zod

[x] pnpm add qrcode
[x] pnpm add @types/qrcode
[x] pnpm add clsx tailwind-merge
[x] pnpm add lucide-react
[x] pnpm add sonner          (toast notifications)
[x] pnpm add date-fns
[x] pnpm add -D @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin prettier eslint-config-prettier

--- 1.4  Configure TypeScript (tsconfig.json) ---
[x] Set "strict": true
[x] Set "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true
[x] Confirm "@/*" path alias maps to "./src/*"
[x] WHY: strict mode catches null/undefined bugs before production

--- 1.5  Configure ESLint + Prettier ---
[x] Create .prettierrc: { "semi": false, "singleQuote": true, "tabWidth": 2 }
[x] Add "editor.formatOnSave": true in .vscode/settings.json
[x] Add lint and format scripts to package.json

