================================================================================
PHASE 3 — AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM
================================================================================
Goal: Implement email/password auth for Owners and Scanner Staff using Supabase
      Auth. Staff are invited, not self-registered. Protect all routes by role.

--- 3.1  Supabase Auth Settings ---
[ ] Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Settings:
      Site URL: http://localhost:3000 (update for production)
      Redirect URLs: http://localhost:3000/auth/callback
[ ] Disable "Enable email confirmations" for dev (re-enable for production)
[ ] Enable "Secure email change"

--- 3.2  Auth Pages ---
[ ] Build src/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx:
      - Email + password form (client component)
      - Submit → POST /api/auth/login (server-side, NOT direct Supabase call)
      - On success → redirect based on role (owner → /dashboard, staff → /scan)
      - Show error states with sonner toast
[ ] No public registration page (owners are seeded, staff are invited)
[ ] WHY: Calling signInWithPassword from the browser is acceptable for auth,
    but redirect logic must be server-validated to prevent role spoofing

--- 3.3  Auth Callback Route ---
[ ] Create src/app/auth/callback/route.ts
[ ] Exchange code for session using exchangeCodeForSession
[ ] Redirect to correct dashboard based on role from user metadata

--- 3.4  Server-Side Login API Route ---
[ ] POST /api/auth/login:
      - Validate input with Zod (email, password)
      - Call supabase.auth.signInWithPassword server-side
      - Check user role in profiles table
      - Set session cookie
      - Return { role } so client can redirect
[ ] WHY: Centralising auth logic server-side prevents bypass via DevTools

--- 3.5  Logout ---
[ ] POST /api/auth/logout:
      - supabase.auth.signOut()
      - Clear cookies
      - Redirect to /login

--- 3.6  Middleware Route Protection ---
[ ] In src/middleware.ts:
      - Unauthenticated users → redirect to /login
      - Scanner staff hitting /owner/** → redirect to /scan
      - Owners hitting /scan → allowed (owners can scan too)
[ ] Create a getSession() helper that reads from cookies server-side

--- 3.7  Session Helper Hooks ---
[ ] Create src/hooks/useSession.ts (client hook)
[ ] Create src/lib/auth/getServerSession.ts (server helper for RSC and API)

--- 3.8  Phase 3 Verification Checklist ---
[ ] Owner can log in and is redirected to /dashboard
[ ] Scanner staff can log in and is redirected to /scan
[ ] Unauthenticated user hitting /dashboard → redirected to /login
[ ] Scanner staff cannot access /dashboard (redirected)
[ ] Logout clears session and redirects to /login
[ ] Auth tokens are in httpOnly cookies, NOT localStorage

EXPECTED RESULT: Secure role-aware authentication. No client-side role checks
that can be bypassed. All route guards enforced in middleware.

TROUBLESHOOTING:
  - Redirect loop → middleware matching too broadly, check matcher config
  - Session missing in RSC → ensure updateSession in middleware runs first
  - Role not available → confirm profiles table is populated on sign-up

================================================================================
PHASE 4 — DATABASE AND ROLE ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================
Goal: Design the full PostgreSQL schema in Supabase. Apply Row Level Security.
      Define all roles and their permissions. Generate migration files.

--- 4.1  Core Tables ---

[ ] profiles
      id          uuid  PK references auth.users(id)
      email       text  NOT NULL
      full_name   text
      role        text  NOT NULL CHECK (role IN ('owner', 'scanner'))
      is_active   bool  DEFAULT true
      created_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()
      updated_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()

[ ] sessions  (events/shows/batches)
      id          uuid  PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      owner_id    uuid  references profiles(id)
      name        text  NOT NULL
      description text
      capacity    int   NOT NULL
      starts_at   timestamptz
      ends_at     timestamptz
      is_active   bool  DEFAULT true
      created_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()
      updated_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()

[ ] tickets
      id          uuid  PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      session_id  uuid  references sessions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
      token       uuid  NOT NULL UNIQUE DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      attendee_name  text
      attendee_email text
      is_used     bool  DEFAULT false
      used_at     timestamptz
      scanned_by  uuid  references profiles(id)
      expires_at  timestamptz
      created_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()

[ ] scan_logs  (immutable audit trail)
      id          uuid  PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      ticket_id   uuid  references tickets(id)
      session_id  uuid  references sessions(id)
      scanned_by  uuid  references profiles(id)
      scan_result text  CHECK (scan_result IN ('success', 'already_used', 'expired', 'not_found'))
      scanned_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()
      ip_address  text
      user_agent  text

[ ] staff_invitations
      id          uuid  PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      email       text  NOT NULL
      invited_by  uuid  references profiles(id)
      session_id  uuid  references sessions(id)  (optional: session-scoped access)
      token       uuid  NOT NULL UNIQUE DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
      accepted_at timestamptz
      expires_at  timestamptz NOT NULL
      created_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now()

--- 4.2  Indexes ---
[ ] CREATE INDEX idx_tickets_token ON tickets(token)
[ ] CREATE INDEX idx_tickets_session ON tickets(session_id)
[ ] CREATE INDEX idx_tickets_is_used ON tickets(is_used)
[ ] CREATE INDEX idx_scan_logs_ticket ON scan_logs(ticket_id)
[ ] CREATE INDEX idx_scan_logs_scanned_at ON scan_logs(scanned_at)
[ ] WHY: token lookup happens on EVERY scan — must be O(log n)

--- 4.3  Row Level Security ---
[ ] Enable RLS on ALL tables:
      ALTER TABLE profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
      (repeat for sessions, tickets, scan_logs, staff_invitations)

[ ] profiles RLS:
      - Users can read/update their own row
      - Owners can read all profiles
      - Only service role can insert (via API)

[ ] sessions RLS:
      - Owners can CRUD their own sessions
      - Scanners can SELECT active sessions they are assigned to

[ ] tickets RLS:
      - Owners can CRUD tickets for their sessions
      - Scanners can SELECT tickets (to initiate scan)
      - Scanners CANNOT UPDATE tickets directly (validation is via API only)
      - WHY: direct UPDATE from client would bypass one-time-use logic

[ ] scan_logs RLS:
      - Scanners can INSERT (via API with service role)
      - Owners can SELECT all logs for their sessions
      - Scanners can SELECT their own logs
      - NOBODY can UPDATE or DELETE scan_logs (immutable)

--- 4.4  Database Functions ---
[ ] Create validate_ticket(p_token uuid, p_scanner_id uuid) RETURNS json
      - SECURITY DEFINER (runs as DB owner, bypasses RLS)
      - Atomic: check + mark + log in ONE transaction
      - Returns { success, reason, attendee_name, session_name }
      - WHY: atomicity prevents race condition double-scans

[ ] Create handle_new_user() trigger function
      - Fires AFTER INSERT on auth.users
      - Inserts row into profiles with role from user metadata

--- 4.5  Create Migration Files ---
[ ] Write all DDL in supabase/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_init.sql
[ ] supabase db push   (applies to remote)
[ ] supabase gen types typescript --linked > src/types/database.ts

--- 4.6  Phase 4 Verification Checklist ---
[ ] All tables exist in Supabase Table Editor
[ ] RLS is ON for all tables (yellow lock icon in Supabase)
[ ] validate_ticket function exists in Database → Functions
[ ] Indexes visible in Database → Indexes
[ ] TypeScript types regenerated and match schema
[ ] Test: scanner JWT cannot UPDATE tickets table directly (should get 403)

EXPECTED RESULT: A locked-down, indexed, audit-ready schema where no client
can bypass validation logic. All writes go through controlled server paths.

TROUBLESHOOTING:
  - RLS blocking legitimate reads → check policy conditions carefully
  - Function not found → confirm SECURITY DEFINER and correct schema
  - Type mismatch → regen types after schema change

