================================================================================
PHASE 11 — SECURITY HARDENING
================================================================================
Goal: Make the app resistant to common web attacks and fraud vectors.

--- 11.1  API Security Headers ---
[ ] Add to next.config.js headers():
      X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
      X-Frame-Options: DENY
      X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
      Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
      Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=()
      Content-Security-Policy: (strict, allow supabase CDN)

--- 11.2  Rate Limiting ---
[ ] /api/validate: 30 req/min per scanner IP + user ID
[ ] /api/auth/login: 5 attempts/min per IP
[ ] Use Upstash Redis (Vercel-compatible) or simple DB counter
[ ] Return 429 with Retry-After header

--- 11.3  Input Sanitization ---
[ ] All API inputs validated through Zod schemas
[ ] Reject unexpected fields (use Zod .strict())
[ ] Never pass raw user input to SQL (Supabase client uses parameterized queries)

--- 11.4  QR Token Hardening ---
[ ] Tokens are UUID v4 (122 bits of entropy) — cannot be guessed
[ ] Optional: add HMAC signature to QR payload so tampered codes fail fast
    before hitting DB
[ ] Never log raw tokens in application logs

--- 11.5  Session / Cookie Security ---
[ ] Supabase SSR uses httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookies automatically
[ ] Set __Host- cookie prefix in production for additional binding
[ ] Session expiry: 1 hour for scanners, 8 hours for owners

--- 11.6  Dependency Audit ---
[ ] pnpm audit before deployment
[ ] Set up Dependabot or Renovate for automated dependency updates
[ ] Review Supabase RLS policies after any schema change

--- 11.7  Penetration Test Checklist ---
[ ] Try to access /api/validate without auth → should get 401
[ ] Try to submit a random token → should get not_found, no info leak
[ ] Try to scan as owner → should work (owner has scanner rights too)
[ ] Try to use a revoked scanner account → should get 403
[ ] Try SQL injection via payload field → Zod + parameterized queries block it
[ ] Try to enumerate ticket tokens → rate limiting blocks bulk attempts

--- 11.8  Phase 11 Verification Checklist ---
[ ] Security headers present (check with securityheaders.com in production)
[ ] Rate limiting tested (curl loop to /api/validate)
[ ] All Zod schemas have .strict() where appropriate
[ ] pnpm audit shows 0 high/critical vulnerabilities

