PHASE 12 — DEPLOYMENT
================================================================================
Goal: Deploy to production on Vercel with production Supabase, environment
      variables, and custom domain. Zero-downtime.

--- 12.1  Pre-Deployment Checklist ---
[ ] pnpm build passes with 0 errors
[ ] All TypeScript errors resolved (tsc --noEmit)
[ ] All .env.local variables documented in .env.example
[ ] pnpm audit clean
[ ] supabase db push run against production project

--- 12.2  Vercel Deployment ---
[ ] Push to GitHub main branch
[ ] Connect GitHub repo to Vercel
[ ] Add all environment variables in Vercel dashboard:
      NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
      NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
      SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
      NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL  (your production domain)
[ ] Deploy → check build logs

--- 12.3  Supabase Production Settings ---
[ ] Update Auth → Site URL to production domain
[ ] Add production domain to Auth → Redirect URLs
[ ] Enable email confirmations
[ ] Enable Supabase Vault for secret storage (optional but recommended)
[ ] Set up Supabase backups (daily, PITR if on Pro plan)

--- 12.4  Custom Domain ---
[ ] Add domain in Vercel → Domains
[ ] Update DNS records (CNAME or A record)
[ ] Verify SSL certificate (auto-provisioned by Vercel)

--- 12.5  Post-Deployment Verification ---
[ ] Login flow works on production domain
[ ] QR generation works and QR images load
[ ] Scan flow works on mobile (test with real phone)
[ ] Realtime updates work (test with two devices)
[ ] Check Vercel Functions logs for any runtime errors

--- 12.6  Phase 12 Verification Checklist ---
[ ] Production URL loads without errors
[ ] HTTPS enforced (no HTTP fallback)
[ ] Environment variables are NOT visible in client bundle (check DevTools)
[ ] Scanner staff can only access /scan on production

================================================================================
PHASE 13 — SCALING AND OPTIMIZATION
================================================================================
Goal: Prepare the app for high-concurrent events (1000+ scans/minute).

--- 13.1  Database Optimization ---
[ ] Confirm all indexes are in place (Phase 4.2)
[ ] Run EXPLAIN ANALYZE on validate_ticket function
[ ] Enable Supabase connection pooling (PgBouncer) in project settings
[ ] WHY: Next.js serverless functions open many short-lived DB connections;
    PgBouncer pools them to prevent exhaustion

--- 13.2  Edge Runtime for Validate Route ---
[ ] Consider moving /api/validate to Edge Runtime:
      export const runtime = 'edge'
[ ] Use @supabase/supabase-js with fetch transport (works on Edge)
[ ] WHY: Edge functions are geographically distributed → lower latency scans

--- 13.3  Caching Strategy ---
[ ] Session data: cache for 60s in RSC (use next revalidate)
[ ] Ticket list: cache for 30s (invalidate on generation)
[ ] QR images: Cache-Control: no-store (security — do not cache)
[ ] Dashboard stats: revalidate on scan event via Supabase webhook

--- 13.4  Load Testing ---
[ ] Use k6 or Artillery to simulate 500 concurrent scans
[ ] Target: < 200ms p99 response time for /api/validate
[ ] Monitor: Supabase DB CPU, connection count, function invocations

--- 13.5  Monitoring and Alerting ---
[ ] Set up Vercel Analytics (basic)
[ ] Set up Sentry for error tracking:
      pnpm add @sentry/nextjs
      npx @sentry/wizard@latest -i nextjs
[ ] Alert on: error rate > 1%, validate latency > 500ms, DB connections > 80%

--- 13.6  Future Improvements (Optional) ---
[ ] Multi-tenant support (multiple organizations)
[ ] NFC tag support alongside QR
[ ] Offline-capable PWA with conflict resolution
[ ] Ticket transfer / name change flow
[ ] Webhook notifications on scan events
[ ] White-label branding per event
[ ] Ticket PDF generation with QR embedded
[ ] SMS verification for high-security events
[ ] Apple Wallet / Google Wallet pass generation

--- 13.7  Phase 13 Verification Checklist ---
[ ] Load test passes without errors or DB timeouts
[ ] Sentry captures a test error correctly
[ ] PgBouncer enabled in Supabase dashboard
[ ] Edge runtime on validate route (check Vercel dashboard function regions)

================================================================================
  CROSS-CUTTING CONCERNS (applies to ALL phases)
================================================================================

CLIENT vs SERVER BOUNDARY:
  Run on SERVER (API routes, RSC, middleware):
    - Auth verification
    - Ticket validation
    - QR token generation
    - Role checks
    - Database writes
    - Secret key access
  Run on CLIENT (React components with 'use client'):
    - Camera/QR scanner UI
    - Real-time subscription listeners
    - Form state
    - Toast notifications
    - Chart rendering

SECURITY NON-NEGOTIABLES:
  [ ] Never validate QR codes on the frontend
  [ ] Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to client
  [ ] Never trust client-supplied role or user ID — always read from server session
  [ ] Always use parameterized queries (Supabase client handles this)
  [ ] Always log failed scan attempts (for fraud detection)

ANTI-FRAUD PROTECTIONS SUMMARY:
  [ ] UUID tokens with 122-bit entropy (unguessable)
  [ ] Atomic DB transaction (race-condition-proof)
  [ ] Rate limiting on scan endpoint
  [ ] Immutable scan_logs (cannot delete evidence)
  [ ] Revocable scanner accounts
  [ ] Token expiry tied to session end time
  [ ] IP + user agent logged on every scan
  [ ] HMAC signature on QR payload (optional but recommended)

